OL,3,CBBC's Gerry Adams claim 'probably not
OL,4,Crule breach', expert says
OL,6,FDuring cross-examination by Mr Adams'
OL,7,Fbarrister, Tom Hogan SC, Mr Banatvala
OL,8,Fsaid the BBC programme had not
OL,9,Fportrayed the material from its
OL,10,Fanonymous source as a "fact", and
OL,11,Frather as an "allegation".
OL,13,FHe said that was a subtle distinction.
OL,15,FMr Hogan rejected that assertion,
OL,16,Finsisting that the documentary had
OL,17,Fpresented the claim about Mr Adams
OL,18,Fsanctioning the murder as fact.
OL,20,F"I respectfully disagree," replied the
OL,21,Fwitness.
